  "doc_id": "27934",
  "text": "One can obviously set the NUT charge to zero, N = 0, to find physical configurations. It is in principle possible to write the scalar charges in terms of the physical charges (the mass, the electromagnetic charges and the scalar moduli) but this process is algebraically complicated. For the example of the Kaluza-Klein black hole, an explicit formula in terms of the physical charges could be obtained but involved trigonometric functions [CITATION_1] . For the four-charge Cvetic-Youm black hole [CITATION_2] , it has been stated in [CITATION_3] that one encounters a fifth order polynomial in the inversion algorithm, which therefore cannot be solved by radicals.",
